# NBA Prop Website ŌĆö Frontend Context

When this rule applies, **treat the frontend as the primary scope**. Do not assume backend directives, MCP tools, or execution scripts are required unless the task explicitly involves API contracts, database writes, or calling the data pipeline.

## Stack

- **Next.js 14** (App Router), React, TypeScript
- **Path alias**: `@/` ŌåÆ `src/*` (e.g. `@/app/components/PlayerSearch`, `@/db/schema`)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (theme in `globals.css`: `:root` + `@theme inline`, dark mode via `prefers-color-scheme`)
- **Database**: Drizzle ORM + Neon (`src/db/schema.ts`, `src/db/index.ts`). Connection uses `POSTGRES_URL` and `@neondatabase/serverless`.
- **Charts**: Recharts (bar charts, tooltips, reference lines)
- **Package manager**: pnpm

## Where things live

| What | Path |
|------|------|
| Pages & layout | `src/app/page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `globals.css` |
| UI components | `src/app/components/` ŌĆö PlayerSearch (container), PlayerCard, PlayerChartDisplay |
| API routes | `src/app/api/update-players/route.ts`, `src/app/api/update-props/route.ts` |
| DB schema & client | `src/db/schema.ts` (tables + `PLAYER_STAT_NAMES`, types), `src/db/index.ts` (drizzle + neon) |
| Data helpers | `src/lib/data.ts` (getPlayerData, getPlayerNames, getPlayerExists, getPlayersOverSeasonAvgLast5, etc.). Player list: DB via `getPlayerNames()` (see `directives/features/frontend_data_readiness.md`). |
| Config | `drizzle.config.ts`, `next.config.ts`, `tsconfig.json` |

## Played-only / DNP exclusion

All averages and ŌĆ£last N gamesŌĆØ logic in `src/lib/data.ts` **exclude games where the player did not play**. Filter: only include rows where `minutes_played` (after trim, lowercased) is **not** one of:

- `''` (empty), `'inactive'`, `'inact'`, `'did n'`, `'0'`, `'0:00'`

DB stores DNP as e.g. **"Inact"** (inactive) or **"Did N"** (did not play). The constant `PLAYED_ONLY` and the same `NOT IN (...)` condition are used in: `getPlayerData`, `getTopScorersLastGame`, `getTopScorersLast7Days`, and `getPlayersOverSeasonAvgLast5` (both ranked and season_avg CTEs). When adding new queries that average or count games, use this same filter so season averages match ŌĆ£games actually played.ŌĆØ

## Data flow

- **Player list**: Canonical list from Neon `players` table via **`getPlayerNames()`** in `src/lib/data.ts`. Home page fetches it (cached), passes `playerNames` to `PlayerSearch` for search/datalist. Player page uses **`getPlayerExists(playerName)`** for 404. See `directives/features/frontend_data_readiness.md`.
- **Game data**: User picks a player and optional ŌĆ£last N gamesŌĆØ (5/10/15/20) ŌåÆ `getPlayerData(playerName, limit)` in `lib/data.ts` queries `player_game_stats` + `games` + `players` via Drizzle (played games only, desc by date). Data is shown in `PlayerChartDisplay` and used for hit-rate in `PlayerCard`.
- **Homepage**: `getPlayersOverSeasonAvgLast5(limit)` returns players whose last-5-game average (points) is above their season average (played games only). Rendered by `OverSeasonAvgLast5`; click sets search + game count 5.
- **Inbound writes**: Backend/execution push data via PUT to `/api/update-players` and `/api/update-props` (Bearer `UPDATE_API_KEY`).

## Component roles

- **PlayerSearch** (`"use client"`): Top-level container. State: playerName, selectedStat, propLineInput, gameCount (5/10/15/20), playerData, loading, playerFound. Fetches via `getPlayerData(playerName, gameCount)`, computes hit rate and verdict (useMemo), renders nav, search, ŌĆ£last N gamesŌĆØ buttons, stat/line, PlayerCard, PlayerChartDisplay. When no search: HomeHero, OverSeasonAvgLast5, FeaturedPlayer.
- **PlayerCard**: Presentational. Props: playerName, stat, propLine, hitRate, optional gameCount, verdict. Shows betting signal, your line, hit rate (Over), status (ON FIRE / STRETCH), consistency.
- **PlayerChartDisplay** (`"use client"`): Recharts bar chart. Props: data (PlayerGameLog[]), statKey, propLine. Bars colored OVER/UNDER/PUSH vs line.
- **OverSeasonAvgLast5**: Horizontal list of players over season avg (last 5); click selects player and sets game count to 5.
- **FeaturedPlayer**, **HomeHero**: Homepage hero and featured player (e.g. LeBron) with card + chart.

## DB schema (source of truth: `src/db/schema.ts`)

- Relational: **players**, **games**, **teams**, **player_game_stats** (minutes_played, points, etc.), **prop_markets**, **player_props**.
- **player_game_stats.minutes_played**: string ŌĆö e.g. `"32"`, `"28:30"` when played; `"Inact"`, `"Did N"`, `"0"`, `"0:00"` for DNP (excluded from averages).
- Exported types: `PlayerGameLog`, `PLAYER_STAT_NAMES`, `PLAYER_STAT_TYPE` for stats dropdown and chart.

## API route details

- **Auth**: Both PUT routes require `Authorization: Bearer <UPDATE_API_KEY>` (env: `UPDATE_API_KEY`).
- **update-players**: Expects `PlayerGameLogs[]` (name + gamelogs with DATE, LOCATION, OPPONENT, MP, FG, FGA, etc.). Uses `@vercel/postgres` `sql` template ŌĆö not Drizzle. Conflict: ON CONFLICT (player_name, game_date, opponent) DO UPDATE.
- **update-props**: Expects array of snake_case props; maps to schema and batch-upserts with Drizzle (batch 100). Conflict on (playerName, gameDate, statType).

## When to stay in the frontend

- UI, components, client state, routing, styling
- Reading from the DB via Drizzle in server actions or API routes
- Adding pages/components or API routes that consume existing backend APIs
- Using `getPlayerNames()` / `getPlayerExists()` for player list and validation (no static list; DB is source of truth)

## When to involve the rest of the workspace

- **API contract or DB schema changes**: Align with `directives/infrastructure/neon_schema.md` and backend `nba-data-backend/src/api/update_db/`
- **New data pipeline or scraping**: Use workspace directives and execution/MCP (see AGENT.md) ŌĆö backend scope
- **New API route that triggers backend scripts**: Implementation lives here; orchestration/scripts live in `execution/` and `nba-data-backend/`

## Frontend MCP (optional)

When available, the **nba-website** MCP server exposes:

- **list_frontend_structure**: Returns a tree of `src/` (app, components, api, db, lib). Use to orient before making changes.
- **get_frontend_schema_summary**: Returns tables and columns from `src/db/schema.ts`. Use when adding features that touch the DB.

Server runs from the backend repo: `nba-data-backend/ai-tools/mcp/frontend_mcp.py`. Configure in `.cursor/mcp.json` as `nba-website`.

## Cache & revalidate

- **Homepage and player pages** use `unstable_cache` (tag `player-data`, 24h revalidate). Cached so DB isnŌĆÖt hit on every request.
- **Player list** is loaded from the DB via `getPlayerNames()`; it falls back to `FALLBACK_PLAYER_NAMES` in `src/lib/playerNames.ts` if the DB fails or returns no rows. Revalidating tag `player-data` (e.g. after the pipeline runs) updates the list and all homepage data.
- **After a scrape** (e.g. GitHub Actions), call **POST /api/revalidate** with `Authorization: Bearer <REVALIDATE_SECRET>` or `x-revalidate-secret: <REVALIDATE_SECRET>` to invalidate the cache so the next request gets fresh data. Set `REVALIDATE_SECRET` in env.

